TITLE: Configuring Axios Boot File in Quasar
DESCRIPTION: Sets up a boot file for Axios configuration in Quasar, creating an axios instance with custom baseURL and making it globally available in Vue components through app.config.globalProperties.
SOURCE: https://github.com/quasarframework/quasar.git/blob/dev/docs/src/pages/quasar-cli-webpack/ajax-requests.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { defineBoot } from '#q-app/wrappers'
import axios from 'axios'

const api = axios.create({ baseURL: 'https://api.example.com' })

export default defineBoot(({ app }) => {
  // for use inside Vue files (Options API) through this.$axios and this.$api

  app.config.globalProperties.$axios = axios
  // ^ ^ ^ this will allow you to use this.$axios (for Vue Options API form)
  //       so you won't necessarily have to import axios in each vue file

  app.config.globalProperties.$api = api
  // ^ ^ ^ this will allow you to use this.$api (for Vue Options API form)
  //       so you can easily perform requests against your app's API
})

export { axios, api }
```

