TITLE: Basic Structure of quasar.config File in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the basic structure of the quasar.config file, exporting a function that receives a context object and returns the configuration object. It shows how to use the context to dynamically configure the app based on the build mode.
SOURCE: https://github.com/quasarframework/quasar.git/blob/dev/docs/src/pages/quasar-cli-vite/quasar-config-file.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { defineConfig } from '#q-app/wrappers'

export default defineConfig((ctx) => { // can be async too
  console.log(ctx)

  // Example output on console:
  /*
  {
    dev: true,
    prod: false,
    mode: { spa: true },
    modeName: 'spa',
    target: {},
    targetName: undefined,
    arch: {},
    archName: undefined,
    debug: undefined
  }
  */

  // context gets generated based on the parameters
  // with which you run "quasar dev" or "quasar build"

  return {
    // ... your config
  }
})
```

