TITLE: Integrating Camera API with Capacitor in Vue Component
DESCRIPTION: Implementation of Capacitor's Camera API in a Vue component for capturing and displaying images. Includes image quality and editing options.
SOURCE: https://github.com/quasarframework/quasar.git/blob/dev/docs/src/pages/quasar-cli-webpack/developing-capacitor-apps/capacitor-api.md#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: html
CODE:
```
<template>
  <div>
    <q-btn color="primary" label="Get Picture" @click="captureImage" />

    <img :src="imageSrc">
  </div>
</template>

<script>
import { ref } from 'vue'
import { Camera, CameraResultType } from '@capacitor/camera'

export default {
  setup () {
    const imageSrc = ref('')

    async function captureImage () {
      const image = await Camera.getPhoto({
        quality: 90,
        allowEditing: true,
        resultType: CameraResultType.Uri
      })

      imageSrc.value = image.webPath
    }

    return {
      imageSrc,
      captureImage
    }
  }
}
</script>
```

