TITLE: Creating Analytics Event and Page Tracking Module in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Defines an analytics module with methods for logging events and page views to Google Analytics through Google Tag Manager's dataLayer. Includes functions for tracking custom events and screen views with optional session ID support.
SOURCE: https://github.com/quasarframework/quasar.git/blob/dev/docs/src/pages/quasar-cli-vite/developing-cordova-apps/managing-google-analytics.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
export default {
  logEvent(category, action, label, sessionId = null) {
    window.dataLayer.push({
      appEventCategory: category,
      appEventAction: action,
      appEventLabel: label,
      sessionId: sessionId
    })
    window.dataLayer.push({ 'event': 'appEvent' })
  },

  logPage(path, name, sessionId = null) {
    window.dataLayer.push({
      screenPath: path,
      screenName: name,
      sessionId: sessionId
    })
    window.dataLayer.push({ 'event': 'appScreenView' })
  }
}
```

