DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use api.extendQuasarConf to extend the quasar.config file. This example shows how to register boot and CSS files, and handle differences between Vite and Webpack configurations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/quasarframework/quasar.git/blob/dev/docs/src/pages/app-extensions/development-guide/index-api.md#2025-04-16_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
export default function (api, ctx) {
  api.extendQuasarConf((conf, api) => {
    // make sure my-ext boot file is registered
    conf.boot.push('~quasar-app-extension-my-ext/src/boot/my-ext-bootfile.js')

    if (api.hasVite !== true) {
      // make sure boot file transpiles
      conf.build.webpackTranspileDependencies.push(/quasar-app-extension-my-ext[\/]src[\/]boot/)
      // if boot file imports anything, make sure that
      // the regex above matches those files too!
    }

    // make sure my-ext css goes through webpack
    conf.css.push('~quasar-app-extension-my-ext/src/component/my-ext.sass')
  })
}
```

