TITLE: Implementing Content Script for Web Page Injection in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code creates an IFrame to inject a Quasar app into a web page, handling events for resizing and toggling the drawer. It demonstrates how to create a bridge between the content script and the Quasar app.
SOURCE: https://github.com/quasarframework/quasar.git/blob/dev/docs/src/pages/quasar-cli-vite/developing-browser-extensions/types-of-bex.md#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { createBridge } from '#q-app/bex/content'

const bridge = createBridge({ debug: false });

bridge.on('wb.drawer.toggle', ({ data, respond }) => {
  if (data.open) {
    setIFrameHeight('100%')
  } else {
    resetIFrameHeight()
  }
  respond()
})

const iFrame = document.createElement('iframe')
const defaultFrameHeight = '62px'

function setIFrameHeight (height) {
  iFrame.height = height
}

function resetIFrameHeight () {
  setIFrameHeight(defaultFrameHeight)
}

iFrame.id = 'bex-app-iframe'
iFrame.width = '100%'
resetIFrameHeight()

Object.assign(iFrame.style, {
  position: 'fixed',
  top: '0',
  right: '0',
  bottom: '0',
  left: '0',
  border: '0',
  zIndex: '9999999',
  overflow: 'visible'
})

;(function () {
  iFrame.src = chrome.runtime.getURL('www/index.html')
  document.body.prepend(iFrame)
})()
```

