TITLE: Scroll to Element Helper (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Example function demonstrating how to scroll to a specific element within its container using Quasar scroll utilities.
SOURCE: https://github.com/quasarframework/quasar.git/blob/dev/docs/src/pages/quasar-utils/scrolling-utils.md#2025-04-16_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { scroll } from 'quasar'
const { getScrollTarget, setVerticalScrollPosition } = scroll

// takes an element object
function scrollToElement (el) {
  const target = getScrollTarget(el)
  const offset = el.offsetTop
  const duration = 1000
  setVerticalScrollPosition(target, offset, duration)
}
```

