DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to define a Vue directive that works with SSR by implementing both client-side and server-side logic. The directive sets an element's ID attribute based on the binding value.
SOURCE: https://github.com/quasarframework/quasar.git/blob/dev/docs/src/pages/quasar-cli-vite/developing-ssr/vue-ssr-directives.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const myDirective = {
  mounted (el, binding) {
    // client-side implementation:
    // directly update the DOM
    el.id = binding.value
  },

  getSSRProps (binding) {
    // server-side implementation:
    // return the props to be rendered.
    // getSSRProps only receives the directive binding.
    return {
      id: binding.value
    }
  }
}
```

