TITLE: Integrating serverless-http Package with Quasar SSR
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use the serverless-http package with Quasar SSR to convert Express-style middleware to AWS Lambda compatible handlers. It requires manual installation of the serverless-http package and properly adapts the app object for serverless environments.
SOURCE: https://github.com/quasarframework/quasar.git/blob/dev/docs/src/pages/quasar-cli-vite/developing-ssr/ssr-webserver.md#2025-04-16_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { defineSsrListen } from '#q-app/wrappers'
import serverless from 'serverless-http'

export const listen = defineSsrListen(({ app, devHttpsApp, port }) => {
  if (process.env.DEV) {
    // for dev, start listening on the created server
    const server = devHttpsApp || app;
    return server.listen(port, () => {
      // we're ready to serve clients
    })
  }
  else { // in production
    return { handler: serverless(app) }
  }
})
```

