TITLE: Proper Vue Render Function Caching Pattern
DESCRIPTION: Example showing the correct way to cache properties in Vue render functions to avoid tampering with Vue's DOM diff algorithm.
SOURCE: https://github.com/quasarframework/quasar.git/blob/dev/docs/src/pages/vue-composables/use-render-cache.md#2025-04-16_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// DON'T cache like this:
h(
  'div',
  getCache(`node#${ i }`, () => {
    return {
      onClick () => { console.log(`clicked on node ${ i }`) }
    }
  })
)

// ..rather, do it like this:
h(
  'div',
  { // new such object needs to be created on each
    // render, even if the content is cached
    ...getCache(`node#${ i }`, () => {
      return {
        onClick () => { console.log(`clicked on node ${ i }`) }
      }
    })
  }
)
```

