TITLE: Exporting Serverless Handler for SSR in Quasar Framework
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to configure the SSR listen function to export a handler for serverless environments while maintaining development server functionality. It uses the defineSsrListen wrapper to handle both development and production scenarios.
SOURCE: https://github.com/quasarframework/quasar.git/blob/dev/docs/src/pages/quasar-cli-webpack/developing-ssr/ssr-webserver.md#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { defineSsrListen } from '#q-app/wrappers'
export const listen = defineSsrListen(({ app, devHttpsApp, port }) => {
  if (process.env.DEV) {
    // for dev, start listening on the created server
    const server = devHttpsApp || app;
    return server.listen(port, () => {
      // we're ready to serve clients
    })
  }
  else { // in production
    // return an object with a "handler" property
    // that the server script will be named-export
    return { handler: app }
  }
})
```

