TITLE: Configuring Quasar for Custom Component
DESCRIPTION: This function extends the Quasar configuration to include the boot file for the custom component, handle transpilation, and add the component's CSS file.
SOURCE: https://github.com/quasarframework/quasar.git/blob/dev/docs/src/pages/app-extensions/tips-and-tricks/provide-a-ui-component.md#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function extendConf (conf, api) {
  conf.boot.push('~quasar-app-extension-my-component/src/boot/register-my-component.js')

  if (api.hasVite !== true) {
    conf.build.transpileDependencies.push(/quasar-app-extension-my-component[\/]src/)
  }

  conf.css.push('~quasar-app-extension-my-component/src/component/MyComponent.sass')
}
```

