TITLE: Python Flask Upload Server
DESCRIPTION: Flask server implementation for handling file uploads with CORS support.
SOURCE: https://github.com/quasarframework/quasar.git/blob/dev/docs/src/pages/vue-components/uploader.md#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
from flask import Flask, request
from werkzeug import secure_filename
from flask_cors import CORS
import os

app = Flask(__name__)

cors = CORS()
cors.init_app(app, resource={r"/api/*": {"origins": "*"}})

@app.route('/upload', methods=['POST'])
def upload():
    for fname in request.files:
        f = request.files.get(fname)
        print(f)
        f.save('./uploads/%s' % secure_filename(fname))

    return 'Okay!'

if __name__ == '__main__':
    if not os.path.exists('./uploads'):
        os.mkdir('./uploads')
    app.run(debug=True)
```

