TITLE: Implementing Window Control Functions
DESCRIPTION: Vue component setup implementing window control functions using the exposed Electron API.
SOURCE: https://github.com/quasarframework/quasar.git/blob/dev/docs/src/pages/quasar-cli-vite/developing-electron-apps/frameless-electron-window.md#2025-04-16_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
export default {
  setup () {
    function minimize () {
      if (process.env.MODE === 'electron') {
        window.myWindowAPI.minimize()
      }
    }

    function toggleMaximize () {
      if (process.env.MODE === 'electron') {
        window.myWindowAPI.toggleMaximize()
      }
    }

    function closeApp () {
      if (process.env.MODE === 'electron') {
        window.myWindowAPI.close()
      }
    }

    return { minimize, toggleMaximize, closeApp }
  }
}
```

